Defence Secretary Ben Wallace has said Britain will send scores of artillery guns and more than 1,600 anti-tank weapons to Ukraine in the latest supply of Western arms to help bolster its defence against Russia. It comes after outgoing Prime Minister Boris Johnson promised another £1billion of military support to Ukraine last month. The UK is currently providing the second highest level of weapons support for Ukraine after the USA. The UK has committed £2.3billion in military assistance to Ukraine thus far. FOLLOW BELOW FOR UPDATES...